</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-29_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-31_">What is mandatory care worker training?
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-mandatory-care-worker-training--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1678968162576.png?v=1678968166" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-mandatory-care-worker-training--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1678968162576.png?v=1678968166 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-mandatory-care-worker-training--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1678968162576_500x.png?v=1678968166 320w" width="1238" height="825" alt="What is mandatory care worker training? - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="What is mandatory care worker training? - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-32_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-33_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-35_"><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/products/mandatory-training-for-care-staff-and-care-workers-skills-for-care-aligned?variant=7151096070178" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 71, 178);">Mandatory training for care workers</span></i></a> includes subjects that assist care providers in meeting legislative and regulatory requirements. Health and social care providers in England are required to provide mandatory and statutory training to their staff to comply with CQC requirements.
<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-36_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-38_">What is the role of the Care Quality Commission?
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-the-role-of-the-care-quality-commission--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1678968864981.png?v=1678968875" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-the-role-of-the-care-quality-commission--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1678968864981.png?v=1678968875 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-the-role-of-the-care-quality-commission--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1678968864981_500x.png?v=1678968875 320w" width="4000" height="2667" alt="What is the role of the Care Quality Commission? - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="What is the role of the Care Quality Commission? - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-39_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-40_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-42_">As England's independent health and social care regulator, the CQC ensures high-quality care for all service users. Providers are equipped with extensive guidance to assist them in complying with regulatory requirements.
<br><br>Health and social care providers are required to comply with the following requirements by the CQC:
<br>
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-43_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-44_">Ensure that sufficient workers possess the necessary skills and experience to meet the needs of individuals receiving assistance.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-46_">Provide care staff with the support, training, professional development, supervision and appraisals necessary to fulfil their duties.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-48_">Support care staff in obtaining additional qualifications and providing evidence, where necessary, to the appropriate regulatory body to demonstrate compliance with professional standards.
</li></ul><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-50_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-52_">Without these elements, or if social care providers fail to provide satisfactory evidence that they will continue to adhere to the regulations, the CQC can refuse registration.<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-53_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-55_">Mandatory training requirements for care staff
