</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-79_">Equality, Diversity and Human Rights
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-81_">Infection Prevention and Control
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-83_">Manual Handling of Objects
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-85_">People Moving and Handling
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-87_">Food Hygiene/Food Safety Awareness 
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-89_">Safeguarding Adults at Risk
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-91_">Safeguarding Children.
</li></ul><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-93_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-95_">The mandatory training requirements of an organisation depend on the services it provides. All care organisations must provide their staff with health and safety awareness training, including fire safety training.<br> 
<br>Moving and handling training is mandatory, and food safety and hygiene training is required if your staff prepares or serves food. Mandatory training may include data protection/information governance and complaints handling.
